 ShowCellLabel->False,
 TextAlignment->Center,ExpressionUUID->"3981c36d-e580-4f9f-bd2b-2ba491e9de36"],

Cell["1. What is Blackjack?", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"93fa2d07-39d4-4d50-99ba-ff48d8e5b140"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Blackjack is a heads-up card game between a player and the house (the ",
 StyleBox["dealer",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 "). Both parties are dealt two cards from a shared shoe of one or more \
52-card decks. The player's cards are face up; one of the dealer's cards is \
face-up (the ",
 StyleBox["upcard",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 ") and the other is face-down (the ",
 StyleBox["hole card",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 "). The goal is to assemble a hand that ",
 StyleBox["beats the dealer's total without exceeding 21",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ". Cards count at face value; J, Q, K count 10; an Ace counts 1 or 11, \
whichever gives a better total."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"cd3f7419-c6a7-4e51-8fea-12feb6cf6168"],

Cell["\<\
The player acts first, repeatedly choosing one of five actions:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d26707e0-acb0-4cd1-af82-2f9f2e401784"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Hit ",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "take another card;\n",
 StyleBox["Stand ",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "end the player's turn with the current total;\n",
 StyleBox["Double down ",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "double the bet, take exactly one more card, then stand automatically;\n",
 StyleBox["Split ",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "when the two initial cards have equal point value, split them into two \
hands with equal bets; split aces receive one more card each and cannot be \
hit further;\n",
 StyleBox["Surrender ",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "(not in this implementation) forfeit half the bet without playing."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"24bd80f8-e896-48e3-8d59-61e4ecf4551b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Once the player stands or busts on every hand, the dealer turns up the hole \
card and plays a rigid policy: ",
 StyleBox["hit until the total is at least 17",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ". Casinos differ on whether the dealer also hits a soft 17 (\"H17\") or \
stands on it (\"S17\"); both rules are supported here via a checkbox in the \
",
 StyleBox["Options",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " opener. A ",
 StyleBox["natural blackjack",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " \[LongDash] an ace plus any ten-valued card on the initial deal \
\[LongDash] pays 3 : 2; other wins pay 1 : 1; equal totals push (0); the \
player loses the bet on any bust regardless of the dealer's outcome."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4ce4f85d-09b7-4997-8859-32604d61bdf2"],

Cell["2. Cards and visual representation", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"a5ada9f0-f381-4033-90cc-01c659f5ac12"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Each card is stored as a plain association with two keys: ",
 StyleBox["\"value\"", "Input"],
 " (one of ",
 StyleBox["\"A\", \"2\", \[Ellipsis], \"10\", \"J\", \"Q\", \"K\"", "Input"],
 ") and ",
 StyleBox["\"suit\"", "Input"],
 " (one of the four Unicode suit glyphs). A fresh shoe is built by ",
 StyleBox["CreateShoe[n]", "Input"],
 ", which cross-products ranks and suits ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["n", TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->
  "4133db6a-6c6f-4850-a94a-5e32509b3ace"],
 " times and applies ",
 StyleBox["RandomSample", "Input"],
 " for a uniform shuffle. Each face is rendered with pure ",
 StyleBox["Graphics", "Input"],
 " primitives: a white rounded rectangle, rank+suit in the two opposite \
corners, and a per-rank pip layout for 2\[Dash]10, a stylised letter for J / \
Q / K, and one large suit pip for the Ace. The back shows a blue crosshatch \
with a small central medallion."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"618682d6-a3b5-49c2-8024-feb34a13b05b"],

