Cell["3. The mathematics of Blackjack", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"0fa5717a-a505-48ec-9f1b-fc52a9262734"],

Cell["3.1 Probability of a natural blackjack", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"5c65f859-1674-4c5c-91c4-5d984e3b2db1"],

Cell["\<\
From a single freshly-shuffled deck of 52 cards, the probability that the \
player's initial two cards form a natural blackjack is\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7a881a19-0998-44af-a112-35019ed2251e"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"P", "(", "BJ", ")"}], "=", 
   RowBox[{"2", "\[CenterDot]", 
    FractionBox["4", "52"], "\[CenterDot]", 
    FractionBox["16", "51"]}], "\[TildeTilde]", "0.0483"}], 
  TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormula",
 TextAlignment->Center,
 FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->"79b0640b-33b3-436b-83d3-72206f90dd52"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "(four aces, sixteen ten-valued cards, and the order doesn't matter so we \
multiply by two). Blackjack's 3 : 2 payout on this outcome contributes \
roughly ",
 StyleBox["+2.3%",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " to the player's expected return per hand, which is the single largest \
positive term in the house-edge calculation; take it away (some casinos now \
pay 6 : 5) and the edge roughly doubles against the player."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d58cddbc-0905-444a-89b5-176d39b0367d"],

Cell["3.2 Dealer bust probability", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"279c0c41-3ae0-4fb3-9d13-119cff3ea046"],

Cell["\<\
Because the dealer's policy is fixed, the distribution of the dealer's final \
total depends only on the upcard. In the infinite-deck approximation (cards \
drawn with replacement from a full rank distribution) the dealer's hand is a \
Markov chain on (hard total, soft?)-pairs, which we can enumerate exactly by \
recursion:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ec200657-a9ea-4ea0-95c9-d8e85b0c68b4"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"P", "(", 
    SubscriptBox["T", 
     RowBox[{"n", " ", "+", " ", "1"}]], "\[VerticalSeparator]", 
    SubscriptBox["T", "n"], ")"}], "=", 
   SubscriptBox["p", "card"]}], TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormula",
 TextAlignment->Center,
 FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->"f7bd3c7c-acb6-4d09-a4f8-c47fea93d23f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The probability of finishing ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["bust", TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->
  "cc1d22dc-8b5a-4fbf-8f91-ee2ef0d74dcf"],
 " from each starting upcard is plotted below. It is roughly U-shaped \
\[LongDash] the dealer is most dangerous showing 7, 8, 9, 10, or A (where \
bust probability is ~22\[Dash]25%), and most vulnerable showing 4, 5 or 6 \
(bust probability ~40%). This single curve drives almost every asymmetry in \
basic strategy: the player should stand on otherwise-weak totals when the \
dealer is likely to bust, and press the action when the dealer is strong."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c140d945-11f8-486f-a56e-871ab5fe0623"],

