 TextAlignment->Center,ExpressionUUID->"0cf80a4f-4bba-4193-9574-5f25d24a6da7"],

Cell["3.3 Player decisions: the Bellman equation", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"008b573d-615f-4a9e-a39c-10056e5cb704"],

Cell["\<\
From the player's seat, each state is (hand, bet, dealer upcard, remaining \
deck). The optimal value function satisfies the Bellman equation\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e386687f-cd99-446d-8ba9-ce394c1142e6"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox["V", "*"], "(", "state", ")", "=", 
   UnderscriptBox["max", "a"], " ", "\[DoubleStruckCapitalE]", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["V", "*"], "(", "next", ")"}], "\[VerticalSeparator]", 
   "action", "]"}], TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormula",
 TextAlignment->Center,
 FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->"66fa8ae7-95e7-4e45-8b38-11eafd0d46a8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "taken over available actions ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"a", "\[Element]"}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->
  "23447b45-c318-4416-953c-aaf97fc84d5f"],
 " {Hit, Stand, Double, Split, Surrender}. The Stand branch is closed-form \
once the dealer distribution is known,"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"20eeed90-bf9d-4d83-ad5e-1bb939690bd1"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["EV", "stand"], "(", "T", ",", "u", ")"}], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    UnderoverscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
     RowBox[{"T", "'"}], ""], " ", 
    RowBox[{"P", "(", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["T", "d"], "=", 
      RowBox[{"T", "'"}]}], "\[VerticalSeparator]", "u", ")"}], 
    RowBox[{" ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\[CenterDot]", " ", "outcome"}], 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"T", ",", " ", 
        RowBox[{"T", "'"}]}], ")"}]}]}]}]}], 
  TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormula",
 TextAlignment->Center,
 FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->"8e5b030e-c3fa-4593-aef4-67fda85c73e9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"outcome", "(", 
    RowBox[{"T", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"T", "'"}]}], ")"}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->
  "fdda526b-2680-48a8-8978-cfa3dd89712e"],
 " is +1 (win), -1 (loss), or 0 (push). The Hit branch recursively invokes ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["V", "*"], TraditionalForm]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->
  "ab170015-1ab9-4d24-880d-516cb7f6169c"],
 " on the post-hit hand; in the finite-deck case the remaining deck is \
smaller by one card, which is what separates the correctness of the \
infinite-deck basic-strategy table from a composition-dependent optimum."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b5d304c2-8513-496c-b226-7df6d7ab36a6"],

Cell["3.4 The house edge", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"d1cb27bb-cacd-485c-8328-3e345e42fa24"],

Cell["\<\
The house edge is the negative of the optimal player's expected return, \
computed per unit bet over a uniform distribution of starting hands:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d204b72a-f6d4-42dd-b6dc-c2fce9b62fab"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"house", " ", "edge"}], "=", "-", 
   RowBox[{"\[DoubleStruckCapitalE]", "[", "return", "]"}], "\[TildeTilde]", 
   "0.5", "%"}], TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormula",
 TextAlignment->Center,
 FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->"dea9bd7a-70ff-4aa7-b90d-a032a5ac2451"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "with standard Las Vegas rules (6 decks, S17, 3 : 2 blackjack, \
double-on-anything, split to four hands, late surrender allowed). Our \
implementation omits surrender and caps splits at four hands; these \
restrictions push the edge up to roughly ",
 StyleBox["0.6-0.8%",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " for a perfect player. Notable rule variations:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1752ad35-fe4d-42de-9473-0b43c9626856"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["H17 instead of S17: ",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "+0.22% against the player.\n",
 StyleBox["6 : 5 blackjack payout: ",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "+1.39%.\n",
 StyleBox["Single-deck vs six-deck: ",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "~0.4% in the player's favour.\n",
 StyleBox["No double after split: ",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "+0.14%."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d3b4bfce-4d14-4bf2-b14e-909bf5245a8c"],

Cell["4. Basic strategy", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"3ed13dc4-a43c-4405-bb8d-173ab395c23e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Basic strategy is the action that maximises the Bellman value under the \
infinite-deck assumption, tabulated by (player total, dealer upcard). It is \
the correct play in the absence of any information about the shoe \
composition, and is within ~0.03% of perfect composition-dependent play. \
Because this implementation does not expose double/split in the Monte-Carlo \
EV routine, the basic-strategy oracle returns ",
 StyleBox["H", "Input"],
 " or ",
 StyleBox["S", "Input"],
 " only; double and split are still available to the human player via the \
buttons (and the strategy chart shows which 2-card starting hands benefit \
from them)."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a0f54f0f-33cc-4af6-9a92-e38ceca30e5b"],

Cell[BoxData[
 TagBox[GridBox[{
    {
     GraphicsBox[
